Nigerian Army troops deployed in the Exercise AYEM AKPATUMA while on patrol along Dogon Dawa _ Damari road in Kaduna State killed two suspected criminals and recovered two AK 47 rifles. The troops  also recovered three magazines and 88 rounds of 7.62mm special ammunition from the bandits. In a statement signed by the Director Army Public Relations, Brigadier General Texas Chukwu he revealed that  In another development troops deployed along Rigasa Airport road yesterday were ambushed by suspected bandits.  He added that two soldiers were wounded in the encounter and are presently receiving treatment. According to Chukwu the troops successfully repelled an attack by another suspected bandits in Buruku Benue State